<paragraph id="8BD23688A81EFFD0FF5F8B626375FC41" blockId="3.[136,1452,662,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81EFFD0FF5F8B6267D6FC89" bold="true" box="[189,393,806,832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D0BA81EFFD0FE4F8B6264EDFC89" authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" box="[429,690,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminiflora">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81EFFD0FE4F8B6264EDFC89" box="[429,690,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Lycianthes geminiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an herb to shrub with white stellate corollas that occurs in the cloud forests of 
<collectingCountry id="F37A7618A81EFFD0FEA78B0E67C1FCAD" box="[325,414,842,868]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D0BA81EFFD0FD4D8B0E6321FCAD" authority="(Sendtner 1846: 193) Bitter (1919: 494)" authorityName="Bitter" authorityPageNumber="494" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Sendtner" baseAuthorityPageNumber="193" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[687,1406,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heteroclita">
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81EFFD0FD4D8B0E65F6FCAD" box="[687,937,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Lycianthes heteroclita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B79A81EFFD0FC588B0E62C2FCAD" author="Sendtner, O." box="[954,1181,842,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="193 - 195" refId="ref7061" refString="Sendtner, O. (1846) Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung der Familie der Solanaceen, so wie von zwei neuen etwas abweichenden Arten der Gattung Solanum. Flora 29 (13): 193 - 195." type="journal article" year="1846">Sendtner 1846: 193</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B79A81EFFD0FB4D8B0E6321FCAD" author="Bitter, G." box="[1199,1406,842,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919: 494)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but occurs at higher elevations and has a smaller calyx. The relationship between the two species needs study.
</paragraph>
